se\": { \"message_id\": \"uuid\", \"content\": \"Done.\" } }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n- Position = `len(history)` (each entry is a user+assistant pair)\n- User content is tagged union: `Prompt` or `ToolUseResults`\n- Assistant content is tagged union: `Response` (text) or `ToolUse` (tool calls)\n- File modification tool: `fs_write` (observed), `fs_edit` (defensive)\n- Tool args: `path` field has absolute paths\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### 1. Add transcript types to `types.go`\n\nUnexported types (package-internal, following existing pattern):\n\n- `kiroTranscript` — top-level: `conversation_id` + `history []kiroHistoryEntry`\n- `kiroHistoryEntry` — `user kiroUserMessage` + `assistant json.RawMessage`\n- `kiroUserMessage` — `content json.RawMessage` + `timestamp string`\n- `kiroPromptContent` — for unmarshalling `{\"Prompt\": {\"prompt\": \"...\"}}`\n- `kiroToolUseContent` — for unmarshalling `{\"ToolUse\": {...}}`\n- `kiroResponseContent` — for unmarshalling `{\"Response\": {...}}`\n- `kiroToolUsePayload` — `message_id`, `tool_uses []kiroToolCall`\n- `kiroResponsePayload` — `message_id`, `content`\n- `kiroToolCall` — `id`, `name`, `args json.RawMessage`\n\nUse `json.RawMessage` for the tagged unions (user content, assistant content, tool args) — try each variant in helpers rather than custom UnmarshalJSON.\n\n### 2. Create `transcript.go` with parse helpers and constants\n\nFile modification tools constant:\n```go\nvar kiroFileModificationTools = []string{\"fs_write\", \"fs_edit\"}\n```\n\nPure functions (no methods on KiroAgent):\n- `parseTranscript(data []byte) (*kiroTranscript, error)`\n- `extractUserPrompt(content json.RawMessage) string` — returns prompt text or \"\"\n- `extractModifiedFilesFromHistory(entries []kiroHistoryEntry) []string` — deduped file paths\n- `isFileModificationTool(name string) bool`\n- `extractFilePath(args json.RawMessage) string` — checks `path`, `file_path`, `filename`\n- `extractLastAssistantResponse(entries []kiroHistoryEntry) string` — walks backward for last Response\n\n### 3. Add TranscriptAnalyzer methods to `kiro.go`\n\nAll four methods on `*KiroAgent`, following the Gemini pattern (read file → parse → extract):\n\n- **`GetTranscriptPosition(path)`** → `len(t.History)`, return 0 for missing/empty/`{}`\n- **`ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, startOffset)`** → slice `t.History[startOffset:]`, extract file paths via `extractModifiedFilesFromHistory`\n- **`ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset)`** → iterate `t.History[fromOffset:]`, collect `extractUserPrompt` results\n- **`ExtractSummary(sessionRef)`** → `extractLastAssistantResponse(t.History)`\n\n### 4. Add compile-time assertion\n\nIn `lifecycle.go` (matching Gemini's `lifecycle.go:16`):\n```go\nvar _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*KiroAgent)(nil)\n```\n\nUpdate `kiro_test.go:16-19` to add the assertion there too.\n\n### 5. Add tests in `transcript_test.go`\n\nTable-driven tests with `t.Parallel()` and `t.Run`:\n\n- `TestParseTranscript` — valid, empty history, `{}`, invalid JSON\n- `TestExtractUserPrompt` — Prompt variant, ToolUseResults variant, empty\n- `TestExtractModifiedFilesFromHistory` — fs_write paths, non-file tools skipped, dedup\n- `TestGetTranscriptPosition` — empty path, missing file, empty file, placeholder `{}`, normal\n- `TestExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — offset 0, offset > 0, offset >= len, missing file\n- `TestExtractPrompts` — all prompts, with offset, skips ToolUseResults entries\n- `TestExtractSummary` — last Response, skips ToolUse, empty transcript\n- `TestExtractFilePath` — path field, file_path fallback, filename fallback, empty\n\nUse a shared `testKiroTranscript` constant with 4 history entries (2 prompts, 1 tool use with fs_write, 1 tool result + final response).\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nThen manually test with the real Kiro test repo:\n1. Run a Kiro session in `/Users/alisha/Projects/test-repos/kiro-aws`\n2. Check that `.entire/metadata/<s